<h1 class="h1s">Actresses</h1>
<div class="sharethis-inline-share-buttons st-center st-has-labels  st-inline-share-buttons st-animated" style="height:60px;" id="st-1"><div class="st-total ">
  <span class="st-label">98</span>

    Shares

<div class="combi_pagedesc" id="intro"> <p>An actress is a woman who plays character roles in stage plays, motion pictures, or serials on the television. The term is sometimes also used to refer to a female who lends her voice to radio production. Even though theater as a form of cultural and artistic expression began evolving during the ancient times, initially women were not allowed to perform on stage. Acting as a profession was considered immoral and respectable women were prohibited from appearing on stage. This meant that male actors had to portray female characters, though the so-called fallen women like prostitutes and courtesans did perform occasionally. The situation began changing during the 17th century in England when women began to act on stage--Margaret Hughes is credited to be the first female to have graced the English stage. It was during those times that the word ‘actress’ was coined to differentiate female performers from the males. Even though it was increasingly becoming acceptable for women to become actresses, it was not considered a respectable profession till the 20th century in several societies. Times have really changed now with many intelligent, educated and versatile women choosing to pursue the creative field of acting. This section provides you with the biographies, containing trivia, timelines, persona and professional information, of film and stages actresses covering various genres from all over the world.</p> </div>

The beautiful actress, who went on to feature in films like <em>That Hamilton Woman </em>and&nbsp;<em>Ship of Fools</em>, had a troubled personal life and suffered from physical and mental health issues.</p></div></div></article></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="wrapper"><article class="feature col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 eventstart internal_space"><h2 class="ptitle"><span class="number">&nbsp;72&nbsp;</span><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/lucille-dsire-ball-2192.php">Lucille Ball</a></h2><div class="image col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-sm-5 col-xs-12"><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/lucille-dsire-ball-2192.php"><img class="img-responsive combi-profile-img" src="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/thumbs/lucille-ball-3.jpg" alt="Lucille Ball" title="Lucille Ball"></a><div style="text-align:center;"><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Up-Vote-Clicked', 'Lucille Ball']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up like-btn-2192" data-id="2192" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Down-Vote-Clicked', 'Lucille Ball']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down dislike-btn-2192" data-id="2192" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><div class="clear"></div><span class="likes likes-2192">22</span><span class="dislikes dislikes-2192">9</span></div></div><div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-sm-7 col-xs-12 rt-text-display"><div class="desc-q"><b>Famous As: </b>Actress</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthdate: </b>August 6, 1911</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Sun Sign: </b>Leo</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthplace: </b>Jamestown, New York, United States</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Died: </b>April 26, 1989</div><div class="desc descEvent"><p>One of the most popular actresses of the 1960s, Lucille Ball created the sitcom,&nbsp;<em>I Love Lucy,</em> in 1951. In 1962, she started managing the <em>Desilu Productions</em>, becoming the first woman to run a major TV studio. The recipient of two stars on the <em>Hollywood Walk of Fame</em>, Lucille became an inductee of the <em>Television Hall of Fame</em> in 1984.</p></div></div></article></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="wrapper"><article class="feature col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 eventstart internal_space"><h2 class="ptitle"><span class="number">&nbsp;73&nbsp;</span><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/julia-louis-dreyfus-6922.php">Julia Louis-Dreyfus</a></h2><div class="image col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-sm-5 col-xs-12"><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/julia-louis-dreyfus-6922.php"><img class="img-responsive combi-profile-img" src="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/thumbs/julia-louis-dreyfus-1.jpg" alt="Julia Louis-Dreyfus" title="Julia Louis-Dreyfus"></a><div style="text-align:center;"><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Up-Vote-Clicked', 'Julia Louis-Dreyfus']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up like-btn-6922" data-id="6922" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Down-Vote-Clicked', 'Julia Louis-Dreyfus']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down dislike-btn-6922" data-id="6922" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><div class="clear"></div><span class="likes likes-6922">24</span><span class="dislikes dislikes-6922">10</span></div></div><div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-sm-7 col-xs-12 rt-text-display"><div class="desc-q"><b>Famous As: </b>Actress</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthdate: </b>January 13, 1961</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Sun Sign: </b>Capricorn</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthplace: </b>Manhattan, New York, United States</div><div class="desc descEvent"><p>An actress and comedian, Julia Louis-Dreyfus has won more <em>Screen Actors Guild Awards </em>and more <em>Emmy Awards</em> than any other artist in American television history. She helped German and French exiles during World War II. Openly bisexual, she was famous for her androgynous image.</div></div></article></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="wrapper"><article class="feature col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 eventstart internal_space"><h2 class="ptitle"><span class="number">&nbsp;174&nbsp;</span><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/sunny-leone-10205.php">Sunny Leone</a></h2><div class="image col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-sm-5 col-xs-12"><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/sunny-leone-10205.php"><img class="img-responsive combi-profile-img" src="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/thumbs/sunny-leone-1.jpg" alt="Sunny Leone" title="Sunny Leone"></a><div style="text-align:center;"><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Up-Vote-Clicked', 'Sunny Leone']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up like-btn-10205" data-id="10205" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Down-Vote-Clicked', 'Sunny Leone']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down dislike-btn-10205" data-id="10205" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><div class="clear"></div><span class="likes likes-10205">24</span><span class="dislikes dislikes-10205">9</span></div></div><div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-sm-7 col-xs-12 rt-text-display"><div class="desc-q"><b>Famous As: </b>Actress, Model</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthdate: </b>May 13, 1981</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Sun Sign: </b>Taurus</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthplace: </b>Sarnia, Canada</div><div class="desc descEvent"><p>In 2010, Sunny Leone was named among 12 top porn stars by <em>Maxim</em> magazine. for blood cancer.</p></div></div></article></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="wrapper"><article class="feature col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 eventstart internal_space"><h2 She and 35 others co-founded the <strong>Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences</strong>. She contributed immensely to the success of the comedy television series <em>Veep</em>.</p></div></div></article></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="wrapper"><article class="feature col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 eventstart internal_space"><h2 class="ptitle"><span class="number">&nbsp;959&nbsp;</span><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/tatyana-ali-8931.php">Tatyana Ali</a></h2><div class="image col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-sm-5 col-xs-12"><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/tatyana-ali-8931.php"><img class="img-responsive combi-profile-img" src="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/thumbs/tatyana-ali-2.jpg" alt="Tatyana Ali" title="Tatyana Ali"></a><div style="text-align:center;"><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Up-Vote-Clicked', 'Tatyana Ali']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up like-btn-8931" data-id="8931" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Down-Vote-Clicked', 'Tatyana Ali']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down dislike-btn-8931" data-id="8931" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><div class="clear"></div><span class="likes likes-8931">18</span><span class="dislikes dislikes-8931">9</span></div></div><div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-sm-7 col-xs-12 rt-text-display"><div class="desc-q"><b>Famous As: </b>Actress, Singer</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthdate: </b>January 24, 1979</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Sun Sign: </b>Aquarius</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthplace: </b>North Bellmore, New York, United States</div><div class="desc descEvent"><p>Tatyana Ali is an American singer and actress who gained recognition as a child actress, portraying<em> Ashley Banks</em> on the sitcom TV series <em>The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air</em>. She has been accused of workplace harassment.</p></div></div></article></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="wrapper"><article class="feature col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 eventstart internal_space"><h2 class="ptitle"><span class="number">&nbsp;1224&nbsp;</span><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/peri-gilpin-44056.php">Peri Gilpin</a></h2><div class="image col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-sm-5 col-xs-12"><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/peri-gilpin-44056.php"><img class="img-responsive combi-profile-img" src="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/thumbs/peri-gilpin-1.jpg" alt="Peri Gilpin" title="Peri Gilpin"></a><div style="text-align:center;"><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Up-Vote-Clicked', 'Peri Gilpin']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up like-btn-44056" data-id="44056" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Down-Vote-Clicked', 'Peri Gilpin']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down dislike-btn-44056" data-id="44056" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><div class="clear"></div><span class="likes likes-44056">17</span><span class="dislikes dislikes-44056">3</span></div></div><div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-sm-7 col-xs-12 rt-text-display"><div class="desc-q"><b>Famous As: </b>Actress</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthdate: </b>May 27, 1961</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Sun Sign: </b>Gemini</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthplace: </b>Waco, Texas</div><div class="desc descEvent"><p>Peri Gilpin soared to fame with her roles as <em>Roz Doyle</em> in <em>Frasier</em> and <em>Kim Keeler</em> in <em>Make It or Break It</em>. On the personal front, Collins is a spiritual person.</p></div></div></article></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="wrapper"><article class="feature col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 eventstart internal_space"><h2 class="ptitle"><span class="number">&nbsp;1323&nbsp;</span><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/mary-elizabeth-ellis-44549.php">Mary Elizabeth Ellis</a></h2><div class="image col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-sm-5 col-xs-12"><a class="tileLink" href="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/mary-elizabeth-ellis-44549.php"><img class="img-responsive combi-profile-img" src="//www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/thumbs/mary-elizabeth-ellis-1.jpg" alt="Mary Elizabeth Ellis" title="Mary Elizabeth Ellis"></a><div style="text-align:center;"><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Up-Vote-Clicked', 'Mary Elizabeth Ellis']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up like-btn-44549" data-id="44549" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><i onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'CatVote', 'Down-Vote-Clicked', 'Mary Elizabeth Ellis']);" class="fa fa-thumbs-o-down dislike-btn-44549" data-id="44549" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Vote for Your Favourite "></i><div class="clear"></div><span class="likes likes-44549">17</span><span class="dislikes dislikes-44549">3</span></div></div><div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-sm-7 col-xs-12 rt-text-display"><div class="desc-q"><b>Famous As: </b>Actress</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthdate: </b>May 11, 1979</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Sun Sign: </b>Taurus</div><div class="desc-q"><b>Birthplace: </b>Laurel, Mississippi</div><div class="desc descEvent">Mary Elizabeth Ellis is best known as <em>The Waitress </em>from <em>It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia </em>and as <strong>Lisa Palmer</strong> from <em>Santa Clarita Diet</em>. <script type="text/javascript">
(function($) {
	$('#showmore').css({"cursor":"pointer","color":"green","background-repeat":"no-repeat","background-position":"252px 3px","font-size": "14px"});
    $('.award_section').hide();
    $('#showmore').click(function () {
        $(this).toggleClass("open").toggleClass("close");
        $(this).next().toggle();
	$(this).css("display", "none");

    });
	$.fn.scrollPagination = function(options) {
		var pcondition = '["102","104"]';
		var c1 = 	'category_parent';
		var c2 =  "";
		var c3 =	"1";
		var limit = 10;
		var settings = {
			nop     : 10,  		// The number of posts per scroll to be loaded
			offset  : limit,  // Initial offset, begins at 0 in this case
			error   : 'No More Profiles!', // When the user reaches the end this is the message that is
			               		// displayed. You can change this if you want.
			delay   : 0, 			// When you scroll down the posts will load after a delayed amount of time.
			                	// This is mainly for usability concerns. You can alter this as you see fit
			scroll  : true, 	// The main bit, if set to false posts will not load as the user scrolls.
			                	// but will still load if the user clicks.
			sqlcondition: pcondition,
			c1:c1,
			c2:c2,
			c3:c3
		}

		// Extend the options so they work with the plugin
		if(options) {
			$.extend(settings, options);
		}

		// For each so that we keep chainability.
		return this.each(function() {

			// Some variables
			$this = $(this);
			$settings = settings;
			var offset = $settings.offset;
			var busy = false; // Checks if the scroll action is happening
			                  // so we don't run it multiple times

			// Custom messages based on settings
			if($settings.scroll == true) $initmessage = 'Scroll for more or click here';
			else $initmessage = 'View More';

			// Append custom messages and extra UI
			$this.append('<div class="content"><\/div><div class="loading-bar">'+$initmessage+'<\/div>');

			function getData() {
				// Post data to ajax.php
				var url    = '//www.thefamouspeople.com/ajax/page_loader.php';

				$.post(url, {
				    action    : 'scrollpagination',
				    number    : $settings.nop,
				    offset    : offset,
					sqlc  : $settings.sqlcondition,
					c1    : $settings.c1,
					c2    : $settings.c2,
					c3    : $settings.c3,

				}, function(data) {
					var data = data.trim();
					// Change loading bar content (it may have been altered)
					$this.find('.loading-bar').html($initmessage);
					// If there is no data returned, there are no more posts to be shown. Show error
					if(data.length == 0) {
						$this.find('.loading-bar').hide();
						//$this.find('.loading-bar').html($settings.error);
					}
					else {
						// Offset increases
					    offset = offset+$settings.nop;
						// Append the data to the content div
					   	$this.find('.content').append(data);
						//$('img').loadScroll(1);
						// No longer busy!
						busy = false;
					}
				});
			}
			function getDataContent() {
				// Post data to ajax.php
				var url    = '//www.thefamouspeople.com/ajax/page_loader.php';

				$.post(url, {

					action  : 'scrollpagination',
				        number  : $settings.nop,
				        offset  : offset,
					sqlc	: $settings.sqlcondition,
					c1	: $settings.c1,
					c2	: $settings.c2,
					c3	: $settings.c3

				}, function(data) {

					var data = data.trim();

					// Change loading bar content (it may have been altered)
					$this.find('.loading-bar').html($initmessage);

					// If there is no data returned, there are no more posts to be shown. Show error
					if(data.length == 0) {
						$this.find('.loading-bar').hide();
						//$this.find('.loading-bar').html($settings.error);

					}
				});
			}

			getDataContent(); // Run function initially

			// If scrolling is enabled
			if($settings.scroll == true) {
				// .. and the user is scrolling
				$(window).scroll(function() {
					// Check the user is at the bottom of the element
					if($(window).scrollTop() + $(window).height() > $this.height() && !busy) {
						// Now we are working, so busy is true
						busy = true;
						// Tell the user we're loading posts
						$this.find('.loading-bar').html('Loading Posts');
						// Run the function to fetch the data inside a delay
						// This is useful if you have content in a footer you
						// want the user to see.
						setTimeout(function() {
							getData();
						}, $settings.delay);
					}
				});
			}

			// Also content can be loaded by clicking the loading bar/
			$this.find('.loading-bar').click(function() {
				if(busy == false) {
					busy = true;
					getData();
				}
			});
		});
	}

	$.fn.loadScroll = function(duration) {
	var $window = $(window),
	images = this,
	inview,
	loaded;

	images.one('loadScroll', function() {
		if (this.getAttribute('data-src')) {
			this.setAttribute('src',
			this.getAttribute('data-src'));
			this.removeAttribute('data-src');
			if (duration) {

				$(this).hide()
					   .fadeIn(duration)
					   .add('img')
					   .removeAttr('style');
			} else return false;
		}
	});

	$window.scroll(function() {
	inview = images.filter(function() {
		var a = $window.scrollTop(),
			b = $window.height(),
			c = $(this).offset().top,
			d = $(this).height();
		return c + d >= a && c <= a + b;
	});

	loaded = inview.trigger('loadScroll');
	images = images.not(loaded);
    });
	};

function openwin(nm, width, height) {
    var name = nm;
    if (pop && !pop.closed) {
        pop.close();
    }
    pop = eval("window.open('" + name + "','NewWIN','chrome[4],toolbar=no,left=5,top=5,width=" + width + ",height=" + height + ",directories=no,menubar=no,SCROLLBARS=yes,left=2,right=2')");

}

    window.close();
}
